Package: pphy
Title: Fit psychophysic data, extract slopes and PSS and draw plots by subjects and by average.
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: "First Last <first.last@example.com> [aut, cre]"
Description: A set of functions to fit data from a psychophysic experiment with the modelfree package (fit locally). Extract the slopes and the point of subjective equivalence. Return a matrix of plots, one per subject, with the row data and the fitted values as well as a general plot (means per condition across subjects).
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.0),
    plyr,
    modelfree,
    ggplot2,
    grid,
    gridExtra,
    predata
License: CC-BY-NC-SA
LazyData: true
